com.rhizospherejs.gwt.client.meta
Interface AttributeDescriptor

All Known Implementing Classes:
AttributeDescriptor.EmptyDescriptor
public interface AttributeDescriptor

Marker interface to identify classes that can describe Rhizosphere model attributes (see RhizosphereModelAttribute). Classes implementing this interface should also implement one or more of the other HasXX interfaces defined in the com.rhizospherejs.gwt.client.meta package, for each specific characteristic of the attribute they describe.

An example attribute descriptor: 


 public class GroceryObject implements RhizosphereModel {
   private String name;
   private int amount;

   @RhizosphereModelAttribute(descriptor = AmountMetaData.class)
     public int getAmount() {
       return amount;
     }

   public static class AmountMetaData implements
       AttributeDescriptor, HasKind, HasLabel, HasRange {

     @Override
     public RhizosphereKind kind() {
       return RhizosphereKind.RANGE;
     }

     @Override
     public String label() {
       return "The Amount";
     }

     @Override
     public double maxRange() {
       return 100;
     }

     @Override
     public double minRange() {
       return 50;
     }

     @Override
     public double stepping() {
       return 0;
     }

     @Override
     public double steps() {
       return 5;
     }
   }
 }

The above example declares that the amount field of the sample model is of type RhizosphereKind.RANGE, has a given label and its values can extend within the specified range.
